Place has been there since 1948. I remember my grandfather who lived down the block coming back with coffee in the morning for my mother from this diner. It still retains its retro appeal and is still a good little place to get good, reasonably priced and fast breakfast. Great lil diner that is a staple of Mineola's retro history.

Great atmosphere, great staff, always welcoming.  Strongly recommend you try this place.

A historic part of Mineola since 1948, this diner is very nostalgic for me.  The last time I was there was in 1965 as a young high school senior with 3 of my friends looking for a good meal!  That was more than a half a century ago, and the food was as good then as it is now.  You get a real family feeling from Mike and the other wait staff, the food is fresh and tasty.  Enjoy!

Went here with a friend for a quick lunch, and was impressed with the food and the service.  I got the Monte Cristo sandwich, and it was great!  You can't go wrong with turkey and ham sandwiched between two pieces of french toast.  The fries that came with it were good, too.  Crispy and dry, the way anything deep fried is meant to be.  As to the decor: it looked like a typical diner, but it was very clean and nothing looked worn.  The booth seats were comfortable, and the staff seemed able to handle a large lunch crowd.  In total, it took us an hour to eat, from arriving in the parking lot to paying the check.
